
[1]chicane

   CHICANE, n.

   1. In law, shift; turn; trick; cavil; an abuse of judiciary
   proceedings, by artifices, unfair practices, or idle objections, which
   tend to perplex a cause, puzzle the judge, or impose on a party, and
   thus to delay or pervert justice.

   2. In disputes, sophistry; distinctions and subtleties, that tend to
   perplex the question and obscure the truth.

   3. Any artifice or stratagem.

              CHICANE, v.i. To use shafts, cavils or artifices.
